Now we need to provide the fixed_code. The bug is in the toSource method. The fix should handle non-SCRIPT root nodes gracefully. The precondition check should be removed or made conditional. The simplest fix: Instead of precondition check, we can conditionally get the sourceName only if root is a SCRIPT, else use a default source name. Or we can simply remove the Preconditions.checkState for root type and handle gracefully.

But the most minimal fix is to change the precondition to allow non-SCRIPT roots? Actually the precondition is: Preconditions.checkState(root.getType() == Token.SCRIPT); That will throw an exception if root is not SCRIPT. The fix should be to remove that check or make it conditional. Also, the sourceName retrieval and delimiter processing should be done only if root is SCRIPT. So we can wrap the delimiter processing with an if (root.getType() == Token.SCRIPT). Also, the sourceMap.setStartingPosition should be called regardless? That might be fine. The license info also may be on root.

So fix:

    if (options.printInputDelimiter) {
      if (root.getType() == Token.SCRIPT) {
        if ((cb.getLength() > 0) && !cb.endsWith("\n")) {
          cb.append("\n");
        }
        String delimiter = options.inputDelimiter;
        String sourceName = (String)root.getProp(Node.SOURCENAME_PROP);
        if (sourceName != null && !sourceName.isEmpty()) {
          delimiter = delimiter.replaceAll("%name%", sourceName)
              .replaceAll("%num%", String.valueOf(inputSeqNum));
        } else {
          delimiter = delimiter.replaceAll("%num%", String.valueOf(inputSeqNum));
        }
        cb.append(delimiter).append("\n");
      }
    }

Also, the license info check: if (root.getJSDocInfo() != null && root.getJSDocInfo().getLicense() != null) - that is fine regardless of type.

And the sourceMap setStartingPosition: it should be done before code generation, but it uses cb.getLineIndex and getColumnIndex, which are fine.

The bug could also be that the precondition on sourceName being non-null and non-empty may fail if root is not SCRIPT (since sourceName might be null). By wrapping in if (root.getType() == Token.SCRIPT), we avoid that.

Thus, the fix is to add the type check for SCRIPT before doing delimiter replacement.

But note: the original code has Preconditions.checkState(root.getType() == Token.SCRIPT); We remove that check and instead conditionally execute the delimiter logic only for SCRIPT.

